## 5. API Endpoints

### 5.1 Endpoint Table

| Method | Endpoint | Protected | Purpose | LLM Integration | Request Body | Response |
|--------|----------|-----------|---------|-----------------|--------------|----------|
| POST | /api/recordings | Yes | Upload new recording | Yes | {file, userId} | {id, status} |
| GET | /api/recordings | Yes | Get all user recordings | No | - | [{id, title, date}] |
| GET | /api/recordings/:id | Yes | Get single recording | No | - | {id, title, transcription, summary} |
| DELETE | /api/recordings/:id | Yes | Delete recording | No | - | {success, message} |
| POST | /api/recordings/:id/tags | Yes | Add tags to recording | No | {tags[]} | {success, tags} |
| DELETE | /api/recordings/:id/tags/:tag | Yes | Remove tag | No | - | {success, message} |
| GET | /api/search | Yes | Search recordings | No | ?query=text | [{id, title, matches}] |

**Note:** Authentication is NOT listed here because Firebase Auth is handled entirely on the frontend via Firebase SDK. No backend auth endpoints are needed.

### 5.2 Protected vs Unprotected Endpoints

**Authentication (Firebase SDK - Frontend Only):**
- Signup, login, logout handled by Firebase SDK in frontend
- NO backend auth endpoints required
- Firebase token validation can be added to protected endpoints

**Unprotected (Public):**
- Landing page content endpoints (if any)
- Health check endpoints

**Protected (Requires Firebase Auth Token):**
- All CRUD operations on user data
- All data retrieval endpoints
- All LLM processing endpoints

### 5.3 Endpoints Requiring LLM Integration

List endpoints that need LangChain/LLM processing:
- POST /api/recordings (analyze audio with LLM)
- POST /api/recordings/:id/summarize (generate summary)
- GET /api/search (semantic search with embeddings)

